      <h1 class='title'>Road Safety Strategy</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 01 April 2004 vol 419 c99WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_99ws' title='Col. 99WS &mdash; HC Deb 01 April 2004 vol 419 c99WS' name='column_99ws' href='#column_99ws' rel='bookmark'>99WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0419P2-00789'>
        <a name='S6CV0419P2_20040401_CWS_1'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-david-jamieson' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0419P2_20040401_CWS_1' title='Link to this speech by Mr David Jamieson' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-david-jamieson" title="Mr David Jamieson">The Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Transport (Mr. David Jamieson)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0419P2-00789">The Government's road safety strategy<span class="italic">"Tomorrows roads&#x2014;safer for everyone"</span> published in March 2000 included a commitment to evaluate every three years progress on delivery of the strategy and towards meeting the 2010 casualty reduction targets.</p><p id="S6CV0419P2-00790">The first three-year review has been conducted by the Department, in consultation with the Road Safety Advisory Panel, which includes many of the key stakeholders both within and outside Government. I intend to publish the outcome of the review on 7 April 2004 to coincide with World Health Day 2004, the theme of which is the global road safety challenge. Copies of the review report will be placed in the Library of the House.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
